# Prompt History for Commit

## Original User Request
> Build CLI tools for managing Descope resources
> Support both JSON and human-readable text output

## Plan Reference
- Component: Output Formatting
- From Plan: ./sdlc-plan.md
- Type: Backend (Output Formatting Layer)
- Dependencies: Build Configuration, Core Domain Models

## Subagent Dispatches

### Implementation
- Agent: Orchestrator (direct implementation)
- Requirements:
  - OutputFormatter service with format delegation
  - JsonFormatter with Jackson configuration
  - TextFormatter with human-readable output
  - Support for Application, Tenant, User formatting
  - Visual indicators for success/failure
  - CDI ApplicationScoped beans

### Functional Review
- Iterations: 1
- Final Status: Approved
- Key Feedback: Proper delegation pattern, JSON formatting with null exclusion, human-readable text with visual indicators, comprehensive formatting for all domain objects, excellent test coverage.

### Code Quality Review
- Iterations: 1
- Final Status: Approved
- Key Feedback: Clean separation of concerns, Jackson properly configured with Java 8+ modules, security-conscious null exclusion, well-structured text output, comprehensive JavaDoc, tests cover all scenarios including edge cases.
